G_JURIS_ENDEM_DESC: occurs (regularly, as a native taxon) in multiple nations
FORMATTED_FULL_CITATION: American Ornithological Society (AOS). Chesser, R.T., K.J. Burns, C. Cicero, J.L. Dunn, A.W. Kratter, I.J. Lovette, P.C. Rasmussen, J.V. Remsen, Jr., D.F. Stotz, B.M. Winger, and K. Winker. 2018. Fifty-ninth Supplement to the American Ornithologists' Union Check-list of North American Birds. The Auk 135:798–813.
TAX_COM: Larvivora, Cyanecula, and Calliope were formerly (AOU 1983, 1998; Chesser et al. 2010) considered congeneric with Luscinia, but genetic data (Sangster et al. 2010) indicate that Luscinia as previously constituted was polyphyletic and that species in these genera are not true Luscinia. These genera were formerly included in the family Turdidae, but genetic data (Sangster et al. 2010, Zuccon and Ericson 2010) indicate that they belong in the Muscicapidae (AOU 2018).
